 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search QA Engineer - NFRR/CDO - B5 Bank of America 30,594 reviews Charlotte, NC 28202 Full-time Bank of America 30,594 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Job Description: 
The QA Analyst will be part of the overall NFRR QA and Controls team which includes the delivery and execution of QA strategy for the regulatory needs. . The technology team is implementing/migrating to new tools to change the customer UI/UX experience and build data driven strategies and using data science/AI techniques. Candidate should be capable of testing data strategy implementations, lineage and data analysis. This is an opportunity to continuously learn and think creatively to enhance self and team capabilities. 
Responsibilities 
Understand the various data flows in data sourcing, report generation for data reconciliation, aggregation and control checks for data ingestion 
Understand the E2E and UI workflow for regulatory reports and write complex SQL/queries 
Works directly with the QA, Development and BA teams across globe 
Partners with cross business \ functional QA & Controls programs and teams and users 
Builds test plan, functional test suites / test cases and set up test for metadata/ data dictionary, DQ and data mapping validations 
Perform defect management and logging through JIRA 
Define, document, implement and review test criteria for assigned components and lead initiatives 
 Ability to analyze data, find data gaps, test data lineage and find root cause and efficiently communicating and reporting these back to the development and BA teams 
Provide status update and QA summary, readiness and Work with users for executing use cases and Ensuring user acceptance is met. 
Required Skills 
Strong experience in writing SQL and data validation 
Basic Knowledge in UNIX operating system 
Excellent experience in testing or data reconciliation of applications covering UI, services, reporting, ETL and databases. 
A proactive approach to problem solving and think innovatively 
Working knowledge of testing concepts, verification and validation techniques, defect management tools, quantitative methods and measurement programs. 
Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities, with quick adaptation to new technologies, methodologies, and systems 
Work with Global teams and Strong in written and verbal communications and relationship building and takes initiatives 
Knowledge of Hadoop, Hive, Impala for query writing 
Plus Skills 
Knowledge of OOPS(Java) and API is plus 
Experience with Test Automation – tools Selenium or cucumber or SOAP 
Experience in software development life cycle (SDLC) process and agile methodology 
Job Band: 
H5 
Shift: 
1st shift (United States of America) 
Hours Per Week: 
